@module diagnostic
@lang aria
@aid_version 0.2
@layer 2
@purpose Diagnostic types, error codes, and rendering for compiler messages
@depends []

---

@type Severity
@kind sum
@variants
  Error — Compilation error, prevents codegen
  Warning — Potential issue, does not prevent codegen
  Info — Informational message
  Hint — Suggestion for improvement
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 10
@purpose Classifies diagnostic urgency. Only Error severity blocks compilation (checked via bag_has_errors); Warning/Info/Hint are advisory. Used throughout the pipeline to decide whether to halt after a phase.
@workflow Every compiler phase (parser, resolver, checker) emits diagnostics with a Severity. The driver checks bag_has_errors after each phase to decide whether to proceed.

---

@type LabelStyle
@kind sum
@variants
  Primary — Main diagnostic location
  Secondary — Related/supporting location
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 25
@purpose Distinguishes the main error site from supporting context locations in rendered output. Primary labels get caret underlines; secondary labels provide cross-reference context.

---

@type Applicability
@kind sum
@variants
  MachineApplicable — Safe to auto-apply
  MaybeIncorrect — May not be correct in all cases
  HasPlaceholders — Contains placeholder text requiring user edits
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 36
@purpose Controls whether a suggestion can be auto-applied by tooling. Modeled after Rust's rustc Applicability enum for IDE integration compatibility.

---

@type Span
@kind struct
@fields
  file: str — Source file path
  line: i64 — 1-based line number
  col: i64 — 1-based column number
  offset: i64 — Byte offset into source
  length: i64 — Span length in bytes
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 49
@purpose Locates a region in source code for error reporting. Carries both human-readable (file:line:col) and machine-usable (offset+length) coordinates. Dual representation avoids recomputation during rendering.
@invariants line and col are 1-based (0 values indicate a sentinel/unknown span). length >= 0. offset is a byte offset from the start of the file content.
@notes The sentinel span (file="", line=0, col=0, offset=0, length=0) is created by _sentinel_span() and used to initialize empty collections where the bootstrap compiler requires a non-empty array literal.

---

@type Label
@kind struct
@fields
  span: Span — Location in source
  message: str — Label text
  style: LabelStyle — Primary or secondary
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 85
@purpose Annotates a specific source location with a message, used to build rich multi-location diagnostics. Multiple labels on one diagnostic enable "defined here" / "used here" style messages.

---

@type Suggestion
@kind struct
@fields
  message: str — Description of the fix
  replacement: str — Replacement text
  span: Span — Location to replace
  applicability: Applicability — How safe to auto-apply
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 102
@purpose Encodes a machine-applicable fix that tooling can offer or auto-apply. The span identifies what to replace; replacement is the new text.
@notes Empty message (len == 0) is used as a sentinel to indicate "no real suggestion" — render_json_diagnostic skips suggestions with empty messages. [src: diagnostic.aria:488]

---

@type Diagnostic
@kind struct
@fields
  code: str — Error code (e.g. E0001)
  severity: Severity — Error, Warning, Info, or Hint
  message: str — Human-readable message
  span: Span — Primary source location
  labels: [Label] — Annotated source locations
  notes: [str] — Additional notes
  suggestions: [Suggestion] — Suggested fixes
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 114
@purpose The central error reporting type. Every compiler diagnostic — from syntax errors to type mismatches — is represented as a Diagnostic. Carries all information needed for both human-readable and JSON rendering.
@invariants labels always contains at least one element (a primary label auto-created from span+message by new_diagnostic). notes and suggestions each contain at least one sentinel element due to bootstrap compiler limitations requiring non-empty array literals. [src: diagnostic.aria:132-134]
@antipatterns Do not check labels/notes/suggestions length to determine if they have real content — they always have sentinel entries. Instead check if element message/text is non-empty.

---

@type DiagnosticBag
@kind struct
@fields
  diagnostics: [Diagnostic] — Collected diagnostics
  error_count: i64 — Number of errors
  warning_count: i64 — Number of warnings
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 145
@purpose Accumulator for diagnostics across a compilation phase. Tracks error/warning counts separately so bag_has_errors is O(1) without scanning the list.
@invariants diagnostics[0] is always a sentinel error (empty code, empty message, sentinel span) — real diagnostics start at index 1. error_count and warning_count reflect only non-sentinel entries. [src: diagnostic.aria:153]
@antipatterns Do not iterate diagnostics starting at index 0 — skip the sentinel. bag_merge and render_json_bag both start iteration at index 1. [src: diagnostic.aria:190, 511]

