@sig (file: str, line: i64, col: i64, offset: i64, length: i64) -> Span
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 57
@purpose Constructor for Span. Thin wrapper around struct literal for API consistency.
@pre line and col should be 1-based for real source locations; 0 indicates unknown/sentinel.

---

@fn span_end_offset
@sig (s: Span) -> i64
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 60
@purpose Computes the exclusive end byte offset of a span (offset + length). Used in JSON rendering to emit the span as a [start, end) pair. [src: diagnostic.aria:444]

---

@fn i2s
@sig (n: i64) -> str
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 64
@purpose Integer-to-string conversion implemented from scratch because the bootstrap compiler stdlib does not provide one. Handles negatives via recursion and decomposes multi-digit numbers digit-by-digit.
@notes Uses recursive decomposition: i2s(n/10) + i2s(n%10). The base case maps single digits 1-9 via an if-chain. This is intentionally simple, not optimized — it is only used for diagnostic rendering, not hot paths. [src: diagnostic.aria:64-79]

