@fn new_suggestion
@sig (message: str, replacement: str, span: Span, applicability: Applicability) -> Suggestion
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 109
@purpose Constructor for Suggestion. Also used to create sentinel suggestions (empty message/replacement) when initializing a Diagnostic. [src: diagnostic.aria:134]

---

@fn new_diagnostic
@sig (code: str, severity: Severity, message: str, span: Span) -> Diagnostic
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 126
@purpose Core Diagnostic constructor. Auto-populates labels with a primary label, notes with one empty sentinel string, and suggestions with one empty sentinel. This ensures array fields are never empty (a bootstrap compiler requirement for array type inference).
@post labels has exactly 1 element (primary label). notes has exactly 1 element (empty string). suggestions has exactly 1 element (empty sentinel).
@notes Callers that need additional labels, notes, or suggestions must construct the Diagnostic manually or modify fields after creation (Aria structs are value types, so this requires reassignment).

---

@fn new_error
@sig (code: str, message: str, span: Span) -> Diagnostic
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 137
@purpose Shorthand for creating an Error-severity diagnostic. The most commonly used constructor across the compiler.

---

@fn new_warning
@sig (code: str, message: str, span: Span) -> Diagnostic
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 140
@purpose Shorthand for creating a Warning-severity diagnostic.

---

@fn new_bag
@sig () -> DiagnosticBag
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 151
@purpose Creates an empty DiagnosticBag with zero counts and a sentinel diagnostic at index 0. The sentinel exists because the bootstrap compiler needs a non-empty array literal to infer the element type [Diagnostic].
@post diagnostics.len() == 1 (sentinel only), error_count == 0, warning_count == 0.

---

@fn bag_add_diagnostic
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag, diag: Diagnostic) -> DiagnosticBag
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 158
@purpose Appends a diagnostic to the bag and increments the appropriate counter. Returns a new DiagnosticBag (immutable/functional style — Aria structs are values).
@notes Severity dispatch uses string comparison via severity_to_str rather than pattern matching — this is a workaround for bootstrap compiler limitations. Only Error and Warning increment counters; Info and Hint are collected but not counted. [src: diagnostic.aria:163-168]
@post error_count or warning_count is incremented by 1 if diag.severity is Error or Warning respectively. diagnostics.len() increases by 1.

---

@fn bag_add_error
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag, code: str, message: str, span: Span) -> DiagnosticBag
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 176
@purpose Convenience function combining new_error + bag_add_diagnostic into one call. The most common way diagnostics are added throughout the compiler.

---

@fn bag_add_warning
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag, code: str, message: str, span: Span) -> DiagnosticBag
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 179
@purpose Convenience function combining new_warning + bag_add_diagnostic into one call.

---

@fn bag_has_errors
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag) -> bool
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 182
@purpose O(1) check for whether any errors were recorded. Used by the driver after each compilation phase to decide whether to proceed or abort.
@workflow Called between pipeline phases: parse -> check errors -> resolve -> check errors -> typecheck -> check errors -> codegen.

---

@fn bag_error_count
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag) -> i64
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 184
@purpose Accessor for the cached error count. Used in format_summary for the final compilation report.

---

@fn bag_warning_count
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag) -> i64
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 186
@purpose Accessor for the cached warning count. Used in format_summary for the final compilation report.

---

@fn bag_merge
@sig (a: DiagnosticBag, b: DiagnosticBag) -> DiagnosticBag
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 188
@purpose Merges bag b into bag a by iterating b's diagnostics (skipping index 0 sentinel) and adding each to a via bag_add_diagnostic. Used when combining diagnostics from separately-compiled modules or sequential phases.
@pre Both bags must have been created via new_bag (i.e., have a sentinel at index 0).
@notes Starts iteration at index 1 to skip b's sentinel. Counts are recomputed incrementally through bag_add_diagnostic, not copied from b. [src: diagnostic.aria:190]

---

@fn format_summary
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag) -> str
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 198
@purpose Formats "N error(s), M warning(s)" summary string for end-of-compilation output.

---

@fn describe_code
@sig (code: str) -> str
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 280
@purpose Maps an error code string (e.g., "E0001") to a human-readable short description (e.g., "unexpected token"). Used in JSON rendering to populate the "description" field. [src: diagnostic.aria:445]
@notes Implemented as a chain of if-statements comparing string equality (no map/dict in bootstrap stdlib). Returns "unknown error code" for unrecognized codes. One code (W0005) is compared as a string literal "W0005" rather than the constant — likely a minor inconsistency. [src: diagnostic.aria:327]
@invariants Must be kept in sync with the error code constants defined at lines 206-278. Adding a new const without a describe_code entry will cause it to return "unknown error code".

---

@fn render_text
@sig (diag: Diagnostic, source: str) -> str
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 371
@purpose Renders a diagnostic as human-readable text with source context, caret underlines, and notes. Produces output similar to rustc's error format: severity[code]: message, file location, source line with carets.
@pre source must be the full source text of the file referenced by diag.span.file. If source is empty or the line is out of range, the source context section is omitted gracefully.
@notes Only renders the primary span's source line — does not render secondary labels' source lines. Underline length defaults to 1 if span.length < 1. Notes with empty strings (sentinels) are skipped. [src: diagnostic.aria:388-389, 400]
@effects Pure — returns a string, no I/O.

---

@fn render_json_diagnostic
@sig (diag: Diagnostic) -> str
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 440
@purpose Serializes a single Diagnostic to a JSON object string. Includes code, severity, message, description (from describe_code), file location, span offsets, labels array, and suggestions array.
@notes JSON is built via manual string concatenation — no JSON library in bootstrap stdlib. Braces are written as escaped strings ("\{" and "\}") because Aria uses {} for blocks. Labels and suggestions with empty messages are filtered out (sentinel skipping). [src: diagnostic.aria:448-449, 468, 488]
@effects Pure — returns a string, no I/O.

---

@fn render_json_bag
@sig (bag: DiagnosticBag) -> str
@source_file src/diagnostic/diagnostic.aria
@source_line 504
@purpose Serializes an entire DiagnosticBag to a JSON object containing a "diagnostics" array and a "summary" object with error/warning counts.
@pre bag must have been created via new_bag (sentinel at index 0).
@notes Starts iteration at index 1 to skip the sentinel diagnostic. [src: diagnostic.aria:511]
@effects Pure — returns a string, no I/O.

